Driver Panel Plan

This file captures the first working plan for the separate driver-facing panel.
The current Drivers module is admin-oriented, so this new panel should focus on
what a driver needs for daily work.

Purpose

- Create a separate driver panel from the admin drivers page.
- Keep the driver experience simple, focused, and role-specific.
- Connect the panel to existing system areas like logbook, inspections, and communications.

Driver Panel Goals

- Let drivers quickly see their assigned vehicle and current status.
- Make pre-trip and post-trip actions easy to complete.
- Allow drivers to manage only their own trips and reports.
- Surface important alerts, reminders, and messages from transport/admin staff.

Recommended Main Sections

1. Driver Dashboard
- Driver name and profile summary
- Assigned vehicle summary
- Current trip status
- Important alerts and reminders

2. My Vehicle
- Vehicle registration number
- Make and model
- Current mileage
- Vehicle condition/status
- Quick access to vehicle details relevant to the driver

3. Pre-Trip Inspection
- Start inspection action
- Inspection checklist
- Defect reporting
- Submission status

4. Trip Log / Journey Management
- Start trip
- Departure location
- Destination
- Purpose of journey
- Odometer start and end
- Fuel used
- Trip remarks
- End trip action

5. My Trip History
- List of trips for the logged-in driver only
- Date, vehicle, route, purpose, distance, and status
- View trip details

6. Reports History
- Pre-inspection history
- Post-trip or issue report history
- Maintenance feedback on reported issues

7. Messages and Notifications
- Messages from transport office
- Reminders for inspections and logs
- Vehicle-related alerts

8. Emergency / Incident Reporting
- Report breakdown
- Report accident
- Report unusual vehicle issue

Navigation Recommendation

- Dashboard
- My Vehicle
- Pre-Trip Inspection
- Trip Log
- History
- Messages
- Profile

What Should Stay Out of the Driver Panel

- Managing other drivers
- Deleting system records
- Service provider management
- Fleet-wide reporting
- Admin-only settings and controls

Suggested Implementation Order

1. Driver dashboard
2. Assigned vehicle view
3. Pre-trip inspection flow
4. Start/end trip log flow
5. Driver history pages
6. Notifications and incident reporting

Current Assumption

- This driver panel will be separate from the current admin Drivers module.
- It will eventually serve logged-in drivers with restricted access to only their own data and actions.
